# Task 4 — Hand Off

## Path Chosen

**Hand Off** — I shared the Flashcard Maker skill file with a friend and had her use it herself, with no extra explanation from me.

## What I Did

1. Took the packaged `flashcard-maker.skill` file (built in Task 1).
2. Sent the file directly to my friend (via chat), without giving her any explanation of how it works or what to type.
3. She loaded/saved the skill on her own account.
4. She then typed a normal, natural-language request on her own — without me telling her the exact trigger phrase.

## Prompt Used (by my friend, independently)

> make flashcard on topic: Impacts of AI on jobs

## Result

The skill triggered automatically on her end and produced flashcards in the exact same format defined in Task 1 (📚 heading + numbered Q&A pairs) — confirming that the skill works correctly for someone else, without any guidance from me.

## How I Verified It

I compared her output with the original Task 1 output format: same heading style, same numbered Q&A structure, same tone. She confirmed it worked correctly and gave her the flashcards she needed on her own topic.

## What Worked / What Didn't

- ✅ My friend was able to use the skill successfully with zero explanation from me.
- ✅ The skill triggered automatically from her own natural-language prompt.
- ✅ Output format was identical to the original — proving the skill is a genuine, portable, reusable asset and not something that only works for me in the original chat.

